<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — When the player lands, it should be able to jump again. Right now it lands but can never jump a second time.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">if player.y &gt;= HEIGHT - 50:
    player.y = HEIGHT - 50
    velocity_y = 0
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Hint:</strong> something needs to flip back to <code>True</code> on landing.</p>
<p><strong>Write the fixed code:</strong></p>
